              <p class="pane-desc">One canonical object namespace under a database root — manifest, wal, tables, snapshots, quarantine, locks — built from typed constructors so no layer assembles its own paths. The layer defines the names; the bytes and policy live above it. The database manifest sits at a fixed path, <code>manifest/current</code>, and an object can be deleted only once it is proven unreachable from there.</p>
